<title>USA: Allen sees Q3 non-cash charge of $0.10/shr.</title>
<headline>Allen sees Q3 non-cash charge of $0.10/shr.</headline>
<dateline>BEACHWOOD, Ohio 1996-10-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Allen Group Inc said Monday it will incur a one-time non-cash charge of $27 million, or $0.10 per share, in the third quarter in connection with its acquisition of Signal Science Inc.</p>
<p>Allen, which supplies the two-way wireless communications industry, said the charge will cover the write-off of in-process research related to its Signal Science acquisition.</p>
<p>Signal Science researches and developes special radio signal equipment for the U.S. government.</p>
